  <title>The Sampling Distribution of the Proportion</title>


<introduction>

  <p>
    So far, the focus in this chapter has been on the distribution of sample means.  However, sometimes we deal with business scenarios where we are counting observations in a sample and in this case the sample proportion (or percentage), <m>\overline{p}</m>, is the statistic that is relevant rather than the sample mean, <m>\overline{x}</m>.
  </p>


</introduction>

